terms.medium_def:
A location first mentioned at Rev.1.11; 
only referred to as Philadelphia (Φιλαδέλφεια). § Philadelphia, "love of brother/sister" 
Philadelphia, a city of Lydia, near Mount Tmolus, Rev. 1:11; 3:7*

Tetrarch Herod Philip I living at the time of the New Testament, first mentioned at Mat.14.3; 
referred to as Philip or [ ] (KJV= Philip) (Φίλιππος); 
son of Herod 'the Great'; 
a brother of Ethnarch Herod Archelaus, Herod Antipas I and Herod Philip II; 
husband of Herodias; 
father of Salome.

Tetrarch Herod Philip II living at the time of the New Testament, only mentioned at Luk.3.1; 
only referred to as Philip (Φίλιππος); 
son of Herod 'the Great'; 
a brother of Ethnarch Herod Archelaus, Herod Antipas I and Herod Philip I.
